{
  "id": "jsonbored_metagraphed_1447",
  "repo_name": "jsonbored/metagraphed",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/jsonbored/metagraphed",
  "base_commit": "590dadc06651749fe47f0f5873d15c09e78bccce",
  "pr_number": 1447,
  "issue_number": 1446,
  "issue_title": "fix(api): per-subnet /health/trends accepts unsupported query params (200 instead of 400)",
  "issue_body": "### Component\n\nworkers / analytics API (`workers/api.mjs`)\n\n### Description\n\n`handleHealthTrends` (the per-subnet `/api/v1/subnets/{netuid}/health/trends` route) takes no `url` argument and never calls `validateQueryParams`, so it returns **200** for any unsupported query param. Every sibling analytics route returns **400 `invalid_query`** instead:\n\n- `handleHealthPercentiles`, `handleHealthIncidents`, `handleUptime`, `handleTrajectory` all `validateQueryParams(...)` and `return analyticsQueryError(...)`.\n- Even the **bulk** `/api/v1/health/trends` route (`handleBulkHealthTrends`) rejects stray params.\n\nOnly the per-subnet trends route is missing the guard.\n\n#### Where\n\n`workers/api.mjs` \u2014 dispatch `return handleHealthTrends(request, env, Number(trendsMatch[1]));` (no `url` passed) and `async function handleHealthTrends(request, env, netuid)` (no validation).\n\n#### Concrete trigger\n\n- `GET /api/v1/subnets/7/health/trends?bogus=x` \u2192 **200** (BUG; the param is silently ignored)\n- `GET /api/v1/subnets/7/health/percentiles?bogus=x` \u2192 400\n- `GET /api/v1/subnets/7/trajectory?x=random` \u2192 400\n- `GET /api/v1/health/trends?bogus=x` (bulk) \u2192 400\n\n#### Impact\n\nInconsistent API contract: a client with a typo'd or unsupported param on this one route gets a silent 200 (and the param ignored) instead of the loud 400 the rest of the analytics surface guarantees. The route takes no params (it always returns all configured windows), so any param is unsupported.\n\n#### Proposed fix\n\nThread the resolved `url` into the handler and validate against an empty allow-list, mirroring the bulk route:\n\n```js\nreturn handleHealthTrends(request, env, Number(trendsMatch[1]), resolved.url);\n// ...\nasync function handleHealthTrends(request, env, netuid, url) {\n  const validationError = validateQueryParams(url, []);\n  if (validationError) return analyticsQueryError(validationError);\n  ...\n```\n\nAdd the route to the analytics non-canonical-query rejection test (`?bogus=x` \u2192 400 `invalid_query`).\n\n### Public-safety confirmation\n\nThis report does not include secrets, credentialed flows, private dashboards, or validator-sensitive data.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-22T12:25:13.000Z",
